    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your steak out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Heat a dry, large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat, once the pan is hot, add your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until charred all over then set aside for later</p><p>Tip: Open a window or turn your extraction on, as this may get smoky!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong> to a large plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> to the plate and give everything a good mix up until fully coated in the spices</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice most of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> and finely dice the rest</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely<strong> </strong>and add them to the bowl with the <strong>diced red onion</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>charred</strong> <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely (don't like spice? Deseed your chillies!) and add to the same bowl</p><p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of your<strong> lime[s]</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>charred chilli salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion and pepper are cooking, heat another large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, once very hot, add the <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest, then slice the rested steak finely on a clean board, then add them to the peppers with any juices</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steak is cooking, add your<strong> tortillas</strong> to a plate</p><p>Put the plate in the<strong> microwave </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve up the <strong>tortillas</strong> topped with the <strong>sliced steak</strong>,<strong> peppers</strong> and<strong> onions</strong></p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>soured cream</strong> and <strong>charred chilli salsa</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
